      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. Start by boiling a large pot of salted water and cook the spaghetti until al dente, following the package instructions.\n2. In a large skillet, heat a generous amount of olive oil over medium heat and finely mince 5-6 cloves of garlic, ensuring they are evenly distributed throughout the oil.\n3. Add 1 tablespoon of red chili flakes to the skillet, stirring constantly to evenly coat the garlic and chili flakes with the oil.\n4. Once the garlic and chili flakes are fragrant and slightly golden, add the cooked spaghetti to the skillet, tossing to coat the pasta in the flavorful garlic and chili oil mixture.\n5. Continue to cook the pasta in the skillet for an additional 2-3 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld together.\n6. Remove the skillet from heat and sprinkle freshly chopped parsley over the pasta, tossing gently to combine.\n7. Serve the Spicy Garlic Pasta immediately, garnished with additional parsley if desired, and enjoy the bold flavors of garlic, chili, and olive oil.",
